      "content": "I see. It feels like one side is talking about the end of the world while the other is just talking about money and competition. If you had to weigh them, does the idea of 'speculative risk' actually carry enough weight to justify slowing down progress that could solve massive problems, or is it kind of just an excuse to stall?",
